@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Tracks.UI

@*
    Help content for the Tracks module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Tracks is a project management module with kanban boards, backlogs, sprints, goals, and custom views. Organize and track your projects from start to finish.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Projects &amp; Products</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating a project:</strong> Click <strong>New Project</strong> and set a name, description, and optional color. Projects can represent software products, initiatives, or any tracked work.</p>
        <p><strong>Project dashboard:</strong> Each project has a dashboard showing key metrics, recent activity, and progress.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Kanban Board</h2>
        <p>The kanban board visualizes work items in columns representing status stages (e.g., To Do, In Progress, Done). Drag items between columns to update their status.</p>
        <p><strong>Adding items:</strong> Click <strong>Add Item</strong> in any column to create a new work item. Set a title, description, assignee, priority, and due date.</p>
        <p><strong>Moving items:</strong> Drag and drop items between columns. Status updates are reflected in real time.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Backlog</h2>
        <p>The backlog contains all unassigned work items. Prioritize items by reordering them, and move items from the backlog into sprints or directly onto the board.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Sprints</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating a sprint:</strong> Define a time-boxed sprint with start and end dates. Add items from the backlog to the sprint scope.</p>
        <p><strong>Sprint progress:</strong> Track sprint completion with burndown charts and progress indicators.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Goals</h2>
        <p>Set high-level goals for your projects. Goals can span multiple sprints and are linked to key results for measurable progress tracking.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Custom Views</h2>
        <p>Create custom views to filter and display work items based on your criteria. Save views for quick access from the sidebar.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use the backlog to capture ideas before committing them to a sprint.</li>
            <li>Custom views help you focus on specific priorities or team members.</li>
            <li>Link work items to goals for better alignment tracking.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
